Reinmar von Zweter (also spelled Reymar von Zwetel, Reymar von Zweten, Römer von Zwickau, Ehrenbote, born around 1200 in Zeutern, today known as Ubstadt-Weiher, Germany; died after 1248) was a Middle High German  poet of Spruchdichtung.

Reinmar von Zweter (also spelled Reymar von Zwetel, Reymar von Zweten, Römer von Zwickau, Ehrenbote, born around 1200 in Zeutern, today known as Ubstadt-Weiher, Germany; died after 1248) was a Middle High German  poet of Spruchdichtung.
He started his work as a poet around 1227 in Austria.
Apparently, Reinmar was continuously on the move after 1241.
His last confirmed writing dates to 1248.
Gustav Roethe (1889), "Reinmar von Zweter", Allgemeine Deutsche Biographie (ADB) (in German), vol. 28, Leipzig: Duncker & Humblot, pp.
